WEBVTT

00:01.566 --> 00:04.569
J.R. Jack Randall,
father of Robin Randall.

00:04.613 --> 00:08.225
Number three on the USPIS
most-wanted list. The Big
Tuna.

00:08.269 --> 00:11.402
He has broken more mail and
custom laws than anyone alive.

00:11.446 --> 00:14.101
Well, except
for number one and two.

00:14.144 --> 00:15.798
The man that has the means
to set up

00:15.841 --> 00:17.974
a bogus operation
like this.

00:18.018 --> 00:19.889
I still don't see
how you didn't figure that out.

00:19.932 --> 00:21.630
She told you.
I'm an idiot.

00:21.673 --> 00:23.588
Look, if you want J.R.,
just bring him in here.

00:23.632 --> 00:25.547
Leave us out of it.
He's got nothing to do with us.

00:25.590 --> 00:27.897
[ Scoffs ] Well,
that's not true, is it, Robin?

00:27.940 --> 00:29.725
You know someone
who's been working with him

00:29.768 --> 00:31.944
from the beginning,
don't you?

00:34.599 --> 00:37.646
♪♪

00:39.865 --> 00:42.216
I-I know I missed your birthday,
Gummy Bear,

00:42.259 --> 00:45.697
but Daddy had a little run-in
with the law.

00:45.741 --> 00:47.917
Here, this'll
make it up to you.

00:47.960 --> 00:51.181
This used to belong
to a famous Austrian princess.

00:54.358 --> 00:55.751
[ Sighs ]

01:00.147 --> 01:02.018
She's always be
a princess to me.

01:26.695 --> 01:28.000
Ah.

01:28.044 --> 01:30.960
Why are we hiding
these pretty diamonds?

01:31.003 --> 01:33.354
You tell me, Gummy Bear.

01:33.397 --> 01:36.748
I paid for this crown
with my hard-earned money.

01:36.792 --> 01:40.100
But the U.S. government
says I can't bring it home

01:40.143 --> 01:43.364
unless I pay them
something called a duty.

01:43.407 --> 01:45.409
Duty.
What does that sound like?

01:45.453 --> 01:47.498
-Poo?
-Use your grown-up words.

01:47.542 --> 01:48.891
-Shit?
-That's it.

01:48.934 --> 01:50.197
It's shit.

01:50.240 --> 01:52.851
Why should I give
15% of what I paid

01:52.895 --> 01:56.638
to a bunch of guys who don't
work half as hard as your daddy?

01:56.681 --> 01:59.423
-Does that seem right?
-I guess not.

01:59.467 --> 02:02.600
Exactly. It's just
a great big pile of doody.

02:02.644 --> 02:05.864
♪♪

02:05.908 --> 02:07.562
Hey, there, Gummy Bear.

02:07.605 --> 02:09.781
-Why are you back?
-You're in trouble.

02:10.826 --> 02:13.394
♪ Somewhere behind the skyline

02:13.437 --> 02:15.961
♪ There is a place
I'm thinkin' ♪

02:16.005 --> 02:19.182
[ Distorted music plays ]

02:22.098 --> 02:25.057
[ Playing "Mary Had
a Little Lamb" off-key ]

02:33.936 --> 02:35.981
They seem pretty thick.
Are you sure you can break them?

02:36.025 --> 02:38.462
I can if I believe.

02:38.506 --> 02:41.204
How the hell can the shit show
be here and not Mom?

02:41.248 --> 02:43.293
This is a new low.
Where the hell is she?

02:43.337 --> 02:46.035
I don't know. I texted her,
but she didn't respond.

02:46.078 --> 02:47.689
-Call her.
-Oh, uh,

02:47.732 --> 02:50.213
I deleted the phone
off my phone, for more games.

02:50.257 --> 02:51.823
Delilah, are you ready?

02:51.867 --> 02:54.086
Do I look like I'm ready?

02:54.130 --> 02:55.697
-Um...
-I'm not!

02:55.740 --> 02:57.525
How can I be the Princess
Ninja Starfish of Weird

02:57.568 --> 02:58.656
without my crown?!

02:58.700 --> 03:00.180
Why are you back?
Why now?

03:00.223 --> 03:02.312
Are you sick?
Are you dying?

03:02.356 --> 03:04.358
-They're watching you.
-Who?

03:04.401 --> 03:06.229
Goddamn Postal
Inspection Service,

03:06.273 --> 03:07.578
-that's who.
-Oh, my --

03:07.622 --> 03:09.232
-They know where you live.
-Oh, really?

03:09.276 --> 03:12.322
The post office has my address?
Wow. Color me shocked, Jack.

03:12.366 --> 03:13.845
I don't have time for this.

03:13.889 --> 03:15.107
What time isit?

03:15.151 --> 03:17.501
What? It's --

03:17.545 --> 03:18.633
Wait. No.

03:18.676 --> 03:20.417
Da-- Wai--
That's my phone!

03:20.461 --> 03:23.551
I told you.
People. Listening.

03:23.594 --> 03:25.379
Here.
For a new one.

03:25.422 --> 03:28.077
-Get one of the pre-paid jobs.
-No. I don't want your money.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.601
You keep acting like this,
you're gonna wind up in jail.

03:30.645 --> 03:33.169
I have been clean
for 14 years, okay?

03:33.213 --> 03:34.736
Now, I have to go
to my daughter's school

03:34.779 --> 03:36.433
and watch
her stupid talent show.

03:36.477 --> 03:38.261
But I guess that's something
you wouldn't understand,

03:38.305 --> 03:40.089
because it's
a good-parent thing.

03:40.132 --> 03:42.570
You were never
in a talent show.

03:42.613 --> 03:44.833
Never had any talent.

03:44.876 --> 03:48.750
[ Plays recorder ]

03:48.793 --> 03:50.969
Love you, Beth!

03:51.013 --> 03:54.408
Okay. Next up -- Next up,
we have Delilah,

03:54.451 --> 03:59.804
A.K.A. Princess Ninja
Starfish of Weird.

03:59.848 --> 04:02.720
Whoo!

04:02.764 --> 04:05.245
Where's your crown,
Princess?

04:12.513 --> 04:14.036
[ Grunts ][ Feedback ]

04:14.079 --> 04:15.907
Oy.

04:20.085 --> 04:21.870
A-one, a-two, a-three, four.

04:21.913 --> 04:23.741
[ Tapping ]

04:23.785 --> 04:27.963
♪ It's fun being weird,
it's fine being weird ♪

04:28.006 --> 04:29.704
♪ It's fun being weird

04:29.747 --> 04:32.402
♪ You should try it sometime [ Kazoo playing ]

04:32.446 --> 04:36.450
♪ It's fun being weird,
you should try it sometime ♪

04:38.147 --> 04:41.150
♪ Juggling or even some mime

04:41.193 --> 04:45.763
♪ You know what's even weirder?
I'll give you a refresher ♪

04:45.807 --> 04:50.072
♪ Something that helps
reduce high blood pressure ♪

04:54.729 --> 04:56.165
-So weird.
-Yeah.

04:56.208 --> 04:58.646
It's farting.

04:58.689 --> 05:02.519
♪ What? Don't frown,
it just went down ♪

05:02.563 --> 05:07.219
♪ It's illegal to call your kid
something stupid in China ♪

05:07.263 --> 05:11.746
♪ And girl kangaroos
have three vaginas ♪

05:11.789 --> 05:15.576
♪ Thomas Edison
was afraid of the dark ♪

05:15.619 --> 05:19.623
♪ Which is weird,
'cause he invented the spark ♪

05:19.667 --> 05:22.060
He invented the light bulb,
idiot!

05:22.104 --> 05:25.020
That doesn't rhyme with "dark,"
does it, Jonah?!

05:25.063 --> 05:28.763
God. Such a douche.

05:28.806 --> 05:30.982
♪ My brother
wears orthotics ♪

05:31.026 --> 05:33.681
♪ And I accept him No, I don't.

05:33.724 --> 05:37.946
♪ And he accepts me
for my deviated septum ♪

05:37.989 --> 05:41.863
♪ I don't have many friends,
and I don't win awards ♪

05:41.906 --> 05:44.518
♪ But I'm cool with that
'cause ♪

05:44.561 --> 05:46.737
♪ I can break boards

05:46.781 --> 05:48.348
Boards!!

05:50.393 --> 05:51.786
Hurry up!

05:55.137 --> 05:56.399
Aah!

05:56.443 --> 05:58.183
[ Laughs ]
You suck!

05:58.227 --> 06:00.534
It's 'cause I don't have
my goddamn crown, okay?

06:00.577 --> 06:02.579
[ Laughter ]

06:02.623 --> 06:04.886
[ Yelling ]

06:04.929 --> 06:07.279
Get off
the goddamn stage!

06:07.323 --> 06:09.499
[ Continues yelling ]

06:09.543 --> 06:11.196
Don't look at me!

06:11.240 --> 06:12.546
I've had just about enough
of you today --

06:12.589 --> 06:13.808
I've had enough of you
for a lifetime.

06:13.851 --> 06:15.679
Everything I did in my life
was for you.

06:15.723 --> 06:16.724
I was your mule.

06:16.767 --> 06:18.552
Oh, six times, tops.

06:18.595 --> 06:20.031
And then you made me
a child bride.

06:20.075 --> 06:22.120
You were 16.
That's hardly a child.

06:22.164 --> 06:24.427
-Yeah, but who does that?
-Half the world.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.473
It's not like
you were their real wife.

06:26.516 --> 06:28.213
It was just free money
to pay for college.

06:28.257 --> 06:30.390
Why couldn't you be
a father who made bad puns

06:30.433 --> 06:33.523
and had slightly racist ways of
saying not-that-racist things?

06:33.567 --> 06:35.177
Why couldn't you
just be normal?

06:35.220 --> 06:36.439
[ Scoffs ]

06:36.483 --> 06:39.137
Normalcy is
a quixotic pursuit.

06:41.096 --> 06:43.054
-What?
-Have you been talking to Nate?

06:43.098 --> 06:44.621
-Who?
-My husband.

06:44.665 --> 06:46.449
Which one?
You have so many.

06:46.493 --> 06:48.190
And that's your fault,
not mine.

06:48.233 --> 06:50.279
Nobody else uses that word.

06:50.322 --> 06:53.282
[ Sighs ]

06:53.325 --> 06:55.153
Sweetie, I have your crown.[ Crown clatters ]

06:55.197 --> 06:56.938
Missing your own kid's
talent show

06:56.981 --> 06:58.809
is about the worst thing
you can do as a parent!

06:58.853 --> 07:00.855
I know you're upset,
but it's not that sim--

07:00.898 --> 07:02.726
I'm s-- I'm just --
I'm so sorry, honey.

07:02.770 --> 07:04.162
How did you do?
Did you break the boards?

07:04.206 --> 07:06.556
I broke my [bleep] hands!

07:06.600 --> 07:08.732
Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

07:08.776 --> 07:12.170
Don't ever talk to me again.

07:12.214 --> 07:13.476
Sweetie, uh --

07:13.520 --> 07:14.825
It's okay.
She just needs to fart.

07:14.869 --> 07:16.131
It lowers her cholesterol.

07:16.174 --> 07:17.567
Or blood pressure.
I-I'm not sure.

07:17.611 --> 07:18.612
She's weird.

07:18.655 --> 07:20.831
J.R.! Hey, man!

07:20.875 --> 07:25.357
-How do you know him?
-I-It's -- He's Dad's boss.

07:25.401 --> 07:27.490
-You son of a bitch.
-Relax, Gummy Bear.

07:27.534 --> 07:29.187
A grandfather
has the right to get --No, no! No.

07:29.231 --> 07:31.015
-Shut your mouth right now.
-Grandfather?

07:31.059 --> 07:33.453
Where's your dad?Well, he had some work stuff
to figure out.

07:33.496 --> 07:35.063
Okay. G-Go get your sister
and go home.

07:35.106 --> 07:36.760
I'll be home soon.
All right? Go.

07:36.804 --> 07:38.109
Go. Go.
Wait, hold on.

07:38.153 --> 07:40.808
I need your phone.
I need your phone.

07:40.851 --> 07:42.505
Go.

07:42.549 --> 07:44.681
No, wait. Sweetie,
where's the phone on your phone?

07:44.725 --> 07:46.074
I didn't know
how else to do it.

07:46.117 --> 07:47.684
You were struggling,
you had nothing,

07:47.728 --> 07:49.294
and you wouldn't
take my money.

07:49.338 --> 07:51.645
Uh, well, we still have nothing,
because it was all fake.

07:51.688 --> 07:53.037
Listen to me.

07:53.081 --> 07:54.125
-I'm leaving.
-Good.

07:54.169 --> 07:55.866
Tonight.
For good.

07:55.910 --> 07:57.868
And if you were smart,
you'd come with me.

07:57.912 --> 08:00.523
Get the ass,
and we'll fly to Cu--Hold on. Hold on. What?

08:00.567 --> 08:02.482
The ass.
Let me take it, keep it safe.

08:02.525 --> 08:05.615
Oh, finally. Thank you.
Now I know what you really want.

08:05.659 --> 08:07.182
Oh, no, no.
You don't understand.

08:07.225 --> 08:08.836
-I-I have --
-I'm going to the police.

08:08.879 --> 08:10.751
-The police aren't after me.
-Okay, the mail police.

08:10.794 --> 08:12.927
Don't be stupid. You'll just
be opening yourself up

08:12.970 --> 08:14.624
to a whole series
of federal charges.

08:14.668 --> 08:15.886
Like what?

08:15.930 --> 08:17.801
Customs violations.

08:17.845 --> 08:19.150
Tax evasion.

08:19.194 --> 08:20.717
War profiteering.
It's a long list.

08:20.761 --> 08:22.371
But I don't do
that stuff anymore.

08:22.414 --> 08:24.547
-Possession of stolen property?
-No, you stole it.

08:24.591 --> 08:27.985
You have it.
You don't want to go to jail.

08:28.029 --> 08:30.031
Well, if that's what it's
gonna take to get you
out of my life forever,

08:30.074 --> 08:31.554
then that's fine.
That's what I'll do.

08:31.598 --> 08:33.034
-I won't let you do that.
-Well, you can't stop me.

08:33.077 --> 08:35.036
Listen to me.
I'm your father.

08:35.079 --> 08:37.473
You know what? Why don't you
talk to one of your kids

08:37.517 --> 08:39.649
who actually gives a shit?

08:39.693 --> 08:41.085
Oh, look.
There's one now.

08:41.129 --> 08:43.523
She could use your attention
and your money.

08:43.566 --> 08:46.656
Hey, Vanessa. This asshole
has something to say to you.

08:49.050 --> 08:50.791
Yes?

08:59.713 --> 09:03.586
You should
zip up your jacket.

09:03.630 --> 09:06.284
Makes you look
like a hooker.

09:17.252 --> 09:18.688
-Hey! Come on, hold up.
-Get away from me.

09:18.732 --> 09:20.211
[ Scoffs ]
I wanted to tell you.

09:20.255 --> 09:21.691
You know,
I'm used to this shit,

09:21.735 --> 09:24.128
but poor Nate.
How could you do this to him?

09:24.172 --> 09:25.608
I was gonna tell him.

09:25.652 --> 09:27.479
My husband has one
of the most analytical minds

09:27.523 --> 09:29.960
I have ever seen. Trust me.
He's already figured it out.

09:30.004 --> 09:31.266
Nothing gets past him.

09:31.309 --> 09:34.574
I just don't get it.
I don't.

09:34.617 --> 09:37.577
-What -- What am I gonna do?
-What am Igonna do, Shelly?

09:37.620 --> 09:40.362
Come on, guys. We all knew this
was a bullshit business, right?

09:40.405 --> 09:42.625
-I didn't.
-It's called "Hoax-a-metrics."

09:42.669 --> 09:45.454
It's called H2-- Oh, shit.
How did I miss that?

09:45.497 --> 09:47.412
I was the manager
of worldwide shipping.

09:47.456 --> 09:49.589
I never shipped anything.Yeah, I didn't do too much,
either.

09:49.632 --> 09:51.199
I was home by 3:00 p.m.
every day.

09:51.242 --> 09:52.722
So was I,
and I took a three-hour lunch.

09:52.766 --> 09:53.984
My phone never worked.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.986
My computer
wasn't even plugged in.

09:56.030 --> 09:58.989
God! For someone to manage
this big an operation

09:59.033 --> 10:01.252
at the amount of returns
he had,

10:01.296 --> 10:04.212
that -- that is...

10:04.255 --> 10:06.823
That's quixotic.

10:06.867 --> 10:09.783
Well...
I'm gonna go home.

10:09.826 --> 10:11.262
Got to spend some time
with my kids.

10:11.306 --> 10:13.961
I had a kid.
His name was...

10:14.004 --> 10:15.702
[Voice breaking]
...Bruce.

10:15.745 --> 10:17.138
We're not seeing our kids.

10:17.181 --> 10:18.661
[ Crying ]
I know!

10:18.705 --> 10:20.532
No, no. I --
That's not what I meant.

10:20.576 --> 10:22.534
I-I-I mean
we're gonna stay here,

10:22.578 --> 10:24.145
and we're gonna
figure this shit out.

10:24.188 --> 10:25.450
Together.

10:25.494 --> 10:27.322
All right? As a team.

10:27.365 --> 10:28.802
-[ Shelly whimpering ]
-Okay.

10:28.845 --> 10:30.064
Okay?

10:30.107 --> 10:32.370
♪♪

10:32.414 --> 10:35.156
[ Grunts ] Look. Right now, we
got to start with what we know,

10:35.199 --> 10:38.333
and that ain't a hell of a lot.
So every theory is on the table.

10:38.376 --> 10:40.161
You know,
when J.R. was in the office,

10:40.204 --> 10:41.684
he was always arguing
in Chinese.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.294
-He was.
-O-Or -- Or in Spanish.

10:43.338 --> 10:44.948
That, too.One time, I swear it was Wookie.

10:44.992 --> 10:46.689
Okay, get real.
He's not a [bleep] space ape.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.691
All I'm saying is that
this is a pretty big universe.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.693
And if every theory's
on the table...

10:50.737 --> 10:53.740
♪♪

10:57.047 --> 10:59.223
[ Belches ]

10:59.267 --> 11:01.399
Look, no money in.

11:01.443 --> 11:03.706
Lots of money out.

11:03.750 --> 11:05.708
He is being challenged

11:05.752 --> 11:09.886
by a wealthy, deceased relative
to spend a shit-ton of money.

11:09.930 --> 11:11.888
We got ourselves
a "Brewster's Millions."

11:11.932 --> 11:13.629
Why the Chinese?

11:13.673 --> 11:16.110
Damn it!

11:16.153 --> 11:18.242
China!

11:18.286 --> 11:19.417
[ Dart stabbing ]

11:19.461 --> 11:21.376
China!

11:21.419 --> 11:22.725
They're our new enemies!

11:22.769 --> 11:26.120
Bro, can we play darts?
On the dart board?

11:26.163 --> 11:27.512
What'd you say?

11:27.556 --> 11:30.951
Can we play darts
on the dart board?

11:30.994 --> 11:32.126
Darts?

11:32.169 --> 11:34.868
-Yeah.
-Darts.

11:34.911 --> 11:37.740
Yeah, me and my buddy Bruce
like to play darts.

11:37.784 --> 11:39.829
[ Shelly whimpering ]

11:39.873 --> 11:42.092
Bruce...

11:42.136 --> 11:44.007
How can you think about darts

11:44.051 --> 11:45.748
when thatis happening?

11:45.792 --> 11:48.620
We just like
to play darts.

11:48.664 --> 11:51.798
W-Why are you so mad?

11:51.841 --> 11:53.538
Go ahead, man.

11:53.582 --> 11:55.018
What?

11:55.062 --> 11:56.716
You don't get it, Mike, okay?

11:56.759 --> 11:58.805
I been -- I've been with him
for three months, okay?

11:58.848 --> 12:01.329
And -- And the one thing
he says, family is everything.

12:01.372 --> 12:03.418
Family is important.
And I know that.

12:03.461 --> 12:05.986
But I don't think it's
that kind of family, all
right? I know that world.

12:06.029 --> 12:08.249
I've seen "Goodfellas"
like a hundred times.

12:08.292 --> 12:11.078
I didn't say Italian Mafia.
I said aMafia.

12:11.121 --> 12:13.080
Could be Yakuza.
He speaks Chinese!

12:13.123 --> 12:14.385
-Yakuza.
-Yeah.

12:14.429 --> 12:16.431
-That's China!
-Guys, look at this.

12:16.474 --> 12:18.433
The guy who registered
our domain name,

12:18.476 --> 12:19.521
he lives 6 blocks away.

12:19.564 --> 12:21.741
Ari Voo-- Voo-- Voo-- V--

12:21.784 --> 12:24.134
Shelly, you're in H.R.
How do you pronounce that name?

12:24.178 --> 12:25.875
Sh-Shel--
What is that name?

12:25.919 --> 12:27.616
-Russians.
-He's got to know something.

12:27.659 --> 12:30.880
They always do.Everything bad starts in Russia.

12:30.924 --> 12:32.795
-You're right.
-We should go.

12:32.839 --> 12:34.579
-I hate these guys.
-We should go.

12:34.623 --> 12:36.146
-Let's go.
-Let's go!

12:36.190 --> 12:38.845
♪♪

12:38.888 --> 12:40.716
Here it is.
Here it is.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.326
Here it is.

12:42.370 --> 12:43.850
Ari Voo-- Voo--

12:43.893 --> 12:46.243
Ari Voo-- Voo-- Voo--
What is his name?

12:46.287 --> 12:48.158
We have answers!
We want questions!

12:48.202 --> 12:50.247
-Who do you work for?!
-Ari!

12:50.291 --> 12:51.901
What the hell
is going on out here?

12:51.945 --> 12:53.163
-You Ari?
-Yeah.

12:53.207 --> 12:54.730
-You're Ari?
-Yes.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.254
-Okay, what are you?
-I'm a web developer. Why?

12:57.298 --> 12:59.474
-This guy's ISIS.
-[ Stammers ]

12:59.517 --> 13:00.910
I'm Greek, you moron.

13:00.954 --> 13:02.216
Yeah.[ Cellphone rings ]

13:02.259 --> 13:04.261
Hold on. Hold on,
I'm getting a call.

13:04.305 --> 13:05.785
This could be J.R.
Hold on.

13:05.828 --> 13:07.221
J.R. You're --

13:07.264 --> 13:09.353
